text: Collinstown () is a townland in Fingal north of Dublin in Ireland. It is in the civil parish of Santry, barony of Coolock, County Dublin. The townland is entirely within the perimeter of Dublin Airport, which grew out of Collinstown Aerodrome, originally a Royal Air Force station, which in the Irish War of Independence became Collinstown Camp for internment of Irish republicans.; ; ==References== Category:Townlands of Fingal
title: Collinstown, Santry
